                <note rend="inline" type="source">817.48 Earthquake of 1931/46: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Minister in Nicaragua</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hanna</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-04-02">April 2,
                            1931</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>36. Your telegram filed April 1, 7 a.m. Marine Corps has ordered that Marines due
                    to leave Managua on the <hi rend="italic">Chaumont</hi> tomorrow be retained <pb
                        facs="0909" n="789" xml:id="pg_789"/> in Nicaragua for the present. This
                    will not interfere with the program of reducing the Marines as specified by June
                    1.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Carr</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
